# HandLayout.elm — TINY

Pinned hand layout. Hand cards render at absolute positions
computed from suit-row index + within-row index. Makes each
card's viewport position a pure function of hand contents +
card identity — no DOM lookup needed at replay time.

## Why pinned

Python-originated actions carry no hand-origin coords (Python
has no DOM). At replay time, Elm needs to animate a drag FROM
the hand card TO the pinned board target. Pinning lets Elm
locate "where is the 7H right now" synchronously from pure
data, no Task/getElement ceremony.

## Key exports

- `cardCenterInViewport : Card -> List HandCard -> Maybe Point`
  — the viewport (x, y) of the card's center. Returns Nothing
  if the card isn't in the hand.
- `handLeft`, `handTop`, `suitRowHeight` — layout constants
  shared between the hand renderer and replay synthesizer.

## Layout

Suit rows in `Card.allSuits` order (Heart, Spade, Diamond,
Club). Within a row, cards are sorted by value ascending.
Horizontal pitch = `BoardGeometry.cardPitch`. Vertical pitch
= `suitRowHeight` = `cardHeight + 12`.

## Pointers

- Consumer: `Main.View` renders each card at `cardCenterInViewport`
  coords.
- Consumer: `Main.elm` replay synthesizer reads the same coords
  as the drag origin for hand-to-board actions.
- Complement: `BoardGeometry.boardViewportLeft` / `Top` pin the
  board; the two modules together pin the whole playable area.
